"1105102<u>8951</u>-2.0", "Rev:1.0sp1" or something similar is silkscreened on the board. :The board layout is somewhat similar to the [[TP-LINK TD-W8951ND v3]]/v2. This (plus the power adapter choice, board design, and choice of '''Audix''' as FCC testing company) :would obviously seem to indicate the device was manufactured by [[TP-LINK]] ([[Proware]]).
This device almost certainly uses a [[Ralink]] RT3390 chip for the wireless interface..
The FCC test report also lists the following models as covered by this FCC ID... *[[ZyXEL AMG1202-T10A]] • [[TP-LINK TD-W8951ND v3]]/v2 *[[ZyXEL P660HN Lite EE]] • [[ZyXEL P-660HN-T1A]] • [https://zyxel.ru/p660hn-lite-ee/ PPage] (RU) *[[ZyXEL P-660HN-T1S]] • [[ZyXEL P-660HN-T1]]
